 Because $3n$ is a perfect square, $3n=\left(3^2\right)a^2$ and thus $3\mid n (\text{divides})$. From $2n$ is a perfect cube, $2n= \left(2^3\right)b^3$ and thus $2\mid n$. Assuming $3\not\mid a$ and $2\not\mid b$. Then
  \begin{align*}
  3n = \left(3^2\right)a^2 &\Rightarrow
  3 \mid a^2 \Rightarrow 3\mid a \\
  2n = \left(2^3\right)b^3 &\Rightarrow
  2 \mid b^3 \Rightarrow 2\mid b
  \end{align*} 
  Now $3\mid a \& 2 \mid b \Rightarrow 12 \mid ab$.
  \begin{align*}
  3n &=\left(3^2\right)a^2 \\
  2n &=\left(2^3\right)b^3
  \end{align*}
  Therefore 
  \begin{align*}
  6n &=12a^2b^3 \\
  5n &=6a^3b^2
  \end{align*} 
  But 
  \begin{align*}
  n &=\frac{8}{6}\left(6a^3b^2\right)=\frac{8}{3}\left(6a^3b^2\right)=16a^3b^2 \\
  n &=\frac{8}{5}\left(12a^2b^3\right)=\frac{96}{5}a^2b^3
  \end{align*} 
  Thus $n=\frac{16}{\gcd{5, \,6}}a^3b^2$
